SECTION 2 — SECURITY COMPONENT INTEGRITY (STRICT PROHIBITION)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The Software contains built-in security mechanisms including, but not limited
to, self-integrity verification, anti-screenshot shields, burn-tracking logic,
session encryption protocols, and OS-level security layers ("Security
Components").

  2.1  You are strictly and unconditionally prohibited from modifying,
       disabling, bypassing, circumventing, removing, weakening, or
       tampering with any Security Component in any way, whether directly in
       source code, in a compiled binary, at runtime, or through any
       external tooling, patch, hook, or instrumentation.

  2.2  Any attempt to reverse-engineer the Security Components for purposes
       other than security auditing under Section 1.1 constitutes a direct
       violation of this License.

  2.3  Disclosure of any security vulnerability discovered during permitted
       auditing must be reported privately to the maintainer before any
       public disclosure. Coordinated Vulnerability Disclosure (CVD) is the
       only permitted disclosure model.

